CatDescriptText: Image published in advertisement in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 17, 1945, pg. 9, with text reading: "New Pittsburgh Home of Nationally Famous Adolph's & Victor's Beauty Products.  Open to Serve Western Pennsylvania With the Finest Beauty and Hair Products and Accessories That Can Be Made.  Conveniently Located Downtown, 624 Wylie Avenue, Harrison G. Walker, Manager..."
TitMainTitle: Adolph's and Victor's Beauty Products, with man standing in back of Victor Beauty Supplies truck with Ohio license plate parked on street, 624 Wylie Avenue
